The extract function in leptos_actix takes a handler function as its argument. The handler follows similar rules to an Actix handler: it is an async function that receives arguments that will be extracted from the request and returns some value. The handler function receives that extracted data as its arguments, and can do further async work on them inside the body of the async move block. It returns whatever value you return back out into the server function. #[server(ActixExtract, "/api")]
pub async fn actix_extract(cx: Scope) -> Result<String, ServerFnError> { use leptos_actix::extract; use actix_web::dev::ConnectionInfo; use actix_web::web::{Data, Query}; extract(cx, |search: Query<Search>, connection: ConnectionInfo| async move { format!( "search = {}\nconnection = {:?}", search.q, connection ) }, ) .await
}

