So far we’ve seen how to use the view macro to create event listeners and to create dynamic text by passing a function (such as a signal) into the view. But of course there are other things you might want to update in your user interface. In this section, we’ll look at how to update classes, styles and attributes dynamically, and we’ll introduce the concept of a derived signal . Let’s start with a simple component that should be familiar: click a button to increment a counter. #[component]
fn App(cx: Scope) -> impl IntoView { let (count, set_count) = create_signal(cx, 0); view! { cx, <button on:click=move |_| { set_count.update(|n| *n += 1); } > "Click me: " {move || count()} </button> }
} So far, this is just the example from the last chapter.

